==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Co
<hw>Co</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the chemical formula for <er>cobalt</er>,
a ferromagnetic metal of atomic number 27.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cobalt, atomic number 27.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Co-</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Co-
<hw>Co-</hw> <pr>(k⟦osl⟧-)</pr>. <def>A form of the prefix
<xex>com-</xex>, signifying <xex>with</xex>, <xex>together</xex>,
<xex>in conjunction</xex>, <xex>joint</xex>. It is used before vowels
and some consonants. See <er>Com-</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>CO2</ent>⟦br⟧
